{"parentUuid":"4debb696-b45a-4ff2-9490-79c56b116725","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"fbfb00be-7842-44a6-90e5-9d69b28d10ec","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is using \"cc-Switch\" - I'm not finding any explicit files for it. Let me search more broadly. The user's settings.json shows they're using a proxy at `http://127.0.0.1:15721` which is the cc-Switch proxy. Let me look for cc-Switch configuration more carefully.\n\nLet me check what cc-Switch is. It's likely a tool that proxies API requests and manages model switching. The key issue is that when Claude Code talks to the API proxy, the proxy needs to properly report the model's context window size.\n\nLet me check:\n1. What cc-Switch config files exist\n2. How Claude Code determines context window size for custom providers\n\nLooking at the settings, the base URL `http://127.0.0.1:15721` suggests there's a local proxy running. Claude Code uses the Anthropic API format, and cc-Switch likely translates between Anthropic API and other model providers (like DeepSeek).\n\nThe context window configuration in Claude Code for custom models depends on how the model is configured. Let me look for:\n1. Any `cc-switch` related files\n2. The environment variables that might control context window\n\nActually, looking at the settings.json more carefully:\n- `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` points to a local proxy\n- The proxy handles the model translation\n\nFor Claude Code to know the context window size, the proxy needs to specify it when listing models or in its response headers. The way this works depends on what cc-Switch supports.\n\nLet me search for cc-Switch configuration files or documentation online.","signature":"fbfb00be-7842-44a6-90e5-9d69b28d10ec"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1861,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":61568,"output_tokens":544,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_reque