{"parentUuid":"913c6660-95f2-4a00-8e96-2ab3ed18e182","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"a53386e3-1a2a-424c-9f27-4cc9f0bcdbc9","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see that:\n1. The model name IS now `DeepSeek-v4-pro[1m]` in the cc-Switch proxy (log shows `model=DeepSeek-v4-pro[1m]`)\n2. cc-Switch WAS restarted (startup messages at 12:26:35)\n3. But `/context` still shows 200K\n\nSo the `[1m]` suffix is being sent by cc-Switch to the API, but cc-Switch isn't properly communicating the 1M context window to Claude Code. \n\nThe issue is that cc-Switch uses the `[1m]` suffix to internally recognize the context window size AND to tell Claude Code about it. But looking at the result... the `[1m]` is appearing in the API request URL which means cc-Switch isn't stripping it before sending to DeepSeek!\n\nWait, looking more carefully: the log shows `model=DeepSeek-v4-pro[1m]` in the request URL. This means cc-Switch is NOT stripping `[1m]` before sending to DeepSeek API. But DeepSeek API probably doesn't care / might ignore it.\n\nThe real question is: why isn't Claude Code showing 1M context? \n\nLooking at this from the Claude Code side: Claude Code determines the context window when it receives the model response from the API. When using a custom proxy (like cc-Switch), Claude Code needs to know the context window from either:\n1. An API response header or field\n2. Or configuration\n\nThe `[1m]` suffix approach might be specifically for Claude Desktop's native model configuration (as mentioned in the search results), NOT for the cc-Switch proxy approach. Let me re-read the search result...\n\nFrom the search results:\n> ### 3. Claude Desktop（2025/2026 新版）— 1M 上下文开关\n> 新版 Claude Desktop 支持直接配置模型列表，并提供 **\"Offer 1M-context variant\"** 开关\n\nSo `supports1m: true` is a Claude Desktop config, and `[1m]` suffix is what cc-Switch uses.\n\nBut it's clearly not working. The cc-Switch log shows it's forwarding `model=DeepSeek-v4-pro[1m]` in the URL, but Claude Code still shows 200K.\n\nMaybe cc-Switch needs more configuration. Let me check if there's an advanced setting in cc-Switch for context window, or if the `[1m]` needs to be added somewhere else (like the model name field vs the display name field).\n\nActually, wait. Let me look at this from a different angle. Maybe the issue is that cc-Switch needs to be configured with `ANTHROPIC_MODEL` environment variable or something similar in the settings.json, rather than just in the GUI.\n\nOR maybe the `[1m]` suffix is simply not the right way to configure this in cc-Switch. Let me look at the cc-Switch UI settings more carefully.\n\nFrom the cc-switch settings.json:\n```json\n\"currentProviderClaude\": \"58ed337c-3376-489d-9e02-0c3cc5a46f70\"\n```\n\nThe provider ID is `58ed337c-3376-489d-9e02-0c3cc5a46f70`. The model name is stored in the SQLite database.\n\nI think the issue might be that:\n1. cc-Switch sends the model WITH `[1m]` to DeepSeek API (which is wrong - it should strip it)\n2. OR the `[1m]` syntax is not actually supported by this version of cc-Switch\n\nLet me look at this issue differently. Maybe the proper way to configure context window in cc-Switch is through a different mechanism, not the `[1m]` suffix. Let me check the cc-Switch npm package and documentation more carefully.\n\nActually, let me reconsider the whole approach. The search results mentioned `[1m]` in the context of \"选择模型 → deepseek-v4-flash[1m] 或 deepseek-v4-pro[1m]\" in the quickstart guide. But this might be a cc-Switch internal notation for some versions, or it might only work in newer versions.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe I should add `ANTHROPIC_MODEL` to the settings.json with the model name including `[1m]`, or try `max_context_tokens` directly.\n\nWait, the log actually shows that `[1m]` IS being sent in the model parameter to DeepSeek API:\n```\nmodel=DeepSeek-v4-pro[1m]\n```\n\nThis is WRONG. cc-Switch should strip `[1m]` and only use it internally to set the context window. If it's not stripping it, then either:\n1. This version of cc-Switch doesn't support `[1m]` correctly\n2. OR there's something else going on\n\nLet me check if there are other configuration options. Maybe I should look at the Claude Code settings.json and add `max_context_tokens` directly there.","signature":"a53386e3-1a2a-424c-9f27-4cc9f0bcdbc9"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1654,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":82944,"output_tokens":1259,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"type":"assistant","uuid":"1407718e-2e9a-47ba-8712-8c9a45990bb7","timestamp":"2026-04-29T04:29:33.345Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"D:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"07a593cf-bcb9-4bf9-a969-effe2aaab829","version":"2.1.123","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
