{"parentUuid":"c054fee9-e594-4453-9dac-4e4b4b9f9b57","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"779408af-4efd-483c-840a-a9afdb4f6a06","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know if there are other ways to make Claude Code recognize the 1M context window when using a custom model through a proxy. Let me think about this from first principles.\n\nClaude Code determines the context window from the API. When using a custom base URL, it gets model info from the API responses. Let me think about what approaches might work:\n\n1. **cc-Switch itself** - Maybe there's a different configuration in cc-Switch. Let me check if cc-Switch has an advanced setting or a \"custom context window\" field in its GUI.\n\n2. **Claude Code settings.json** - Maybe there's a `maxContextTokens` or similar setting I can add directly.\n\n3. **Proxy middleware** - Add a layer between cc-Switch and Claude Code that modifies the response to inject 1M context window information.\n\n4. **Use LiteLLM instead of cc-Switch** - LiteLLM has explicit support for `litellm.context_window` configuration.\n\n5. **Set context window in the Anthropic-compatible API response** - When Claude Code queries the model capabilities, the proxy needs to respond with the correct context window. If cc-Switch doesn't support this, maybe we can add a middleware.\n\nActually, let me check the Claude Code settings.json schema more carefully. Maybe there's a `maxContextTokens` setting at the top level (not in env) that can override the detected context window.\n\nLet me also look at whether cc-Switch has any hidden settings or API endpoints we can use to configure the context window.\n\nLet me search for Claude Code settings that control context window.","signature":"779408af-4efd-483c-840a-a9afdb4f6a06"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":249,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":94848,"output_to