{"parentUuid":"c6f692f1-19ca-4e41-a07b-016c1b3a783a","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"93b3f3d3-c039-4516-abdc-106b3c8b1b7e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_00_5PqRaZX3Co5GEM9XE9mdDEtV","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Claude Code settings.json maxContextTokens context window override custom provider 2025 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Add context window and autocompact configuration · Issue #213 · dcellison/kai\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/dcellison/kai/issues/213\"},{\"title\":\"claude-code-best-practice/best-practice/claude-settings.md at main · shanraisshan/claude-code-best-practice\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/shanraisshan/claude-code-best-practice/blob/main/best-practice/claude-settings.md\"},{\"title\":\"Claude Code详细配置指南：settings.json设置、多模型切换与可视化UI配置方法 - CSDN文库\",\"url\":\"https://wenku.csdn.net/doc/azwsf5c5gb9z\"},{\"title\":\"GPT-5.5在claude code自定义上下文长度的方法\",\"url\":\"https://www.locdd.com/t/topic/45015\"},{\"title\":\"Demo Environment and Configuration Management - KodeKloud\",\"url\":\"https://notes.kodekloud.com/docs/Claude-Code-For-Beginners/Getting-Started-with-Claude-Code/Demo-Environment-and-Configuration-Management/page\"},{\"title\":\"配置参考\",\"url\":\"https://claudecn.com/docs/claude-code/reference/settings/#%e4%b8%8b%e4%b8%80%e6%ad%a5\"},{\"title\":\"Model configuration - Claude Code Docs\",\"url\":\"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/model-config\"},{\"title\":\"Configuration File Guide: Complete settings.json Reference\",\"url\":\"https://lzw.me/docs/opencodedocs/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/appendix/config-reference/\"},{\"title\":\"Navigating Claude Code: The Bare Minimum Setup | HackerNoon\",\"url\":\"https://hackernoon.com/navigating-claude-code-the-bare-minimum-setup\"},{\"title\":\"Claude Code CLAUDE.md vs settings.json: which one controls what (and why it matters)\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/subprime2010/claude-code-claudemd-vs-settingsjson-which-one-controls-what-and-why-it-matters-10i3#comments\"}]\n\n# Claude Code Settings: Context Window & Custom Provider Configuration\n\nHere's a comprehensive synthesis of the search results covering `settings.json` configuration for context window overrides and custom provider setup, current through early 2026.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Context Window Control\n\n### Primary Environment Variables\n\nThese are set inside the `\"env\"` block of `settings.json` (or as OS env vars):\n\n| Variable | Purpose | Recommended |\n|---|---|---|\n| **`CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS`** | Hard-limit the context window in tokens (e.g., `\"400000\"` for 400K) | Overrides the default ~200K that Claude Code imposes on non-Anthropic models |\n| **`DISABLE_COMPACT`** | **Must be set to `\"1\"`** for `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS` to take effect. When disabled, automatic compaction and `autoCompactThreshold` are bypassed — you must manage compaction manually. | `\"1\"` |\n| **`CLAUDE_MAX_CONTEXT_WINDOW`** | Passed as `--max-context-window <N>` to the inner Claude process. Default 0 (uses Claude Code's default of 1M). | `\"200000\"` |\n| **`CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT`** | Percentage of context window at which autocompact fires. Default ~83%. Claude Code silently clamps values above ~83%. | `\"80\"` |\n| **`CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT_OVERRIDE`** | Upstream Claude Code env var name for the same autocompact threshold (used by some wrappers). | |\n| **`CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_1M_CONTEXT`** | Set to `\"1\"` to remove 1M context model variants from the model picker entirely. | `\"1\"` |\n\n### Example `settings.json` for a Non-Anthropic Model (e.g., GPT-5.5 with 400K context)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"env\": {\n    \"CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS\": \"400000\",\n    \"DISABLE_COMPACT\": \"1\",\n    \"DISABLE_AUTOUPDATER\": \"1\",\n    \"IS_SANDBOX\": \"1\"\n  },\n  \"enabledPlugins\": {\n    \"document-skills@anthropic-agent-skills\": true,\n    \"superpowers@claude-plugins-official\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\n> **Important:** When `DISABLE_COMPACT=1`, `autoCompactThreshold` is ignored. You must run `/compact` manually or risk exceeding the model's actual context limit.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Model & Provider Configuration\n\n### In `settings.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n  \"alwaysThinkingEnabled\": true\n}\n```\n\n- **`model`**: Accepts aliases (`sonnet`, `opus`, `haiku`), full model IDs, or the special `\"default\"` to clear overrides.\n- Extended context aliases: `sonnet[1m]`, `opus[1m]`.\n\n### Cloud Provider Env Vars (also set in `\"env\"` block)\n\n| Variable | Provider |\n|---|---|\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_BEDROCK` | AWS Bedrock |\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_VERTEX` | Google Vertex AI |\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_FOUNDRY` | Microsoft Foundry |\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_SKIP_BEDROCK_AUTH` | Skip Bedrock auth |\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_SKIP_VERTEX_AUTH` | Skip Vertex auth |\n\n### API Authentication (in `\"env\"`)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"env\": {\n    \"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\": \"sk-ant-api03-...\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"custom-auth-header\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_MODEL\": \"claude-opus-4-7\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_SONNET_MODEL\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_OPUS_MODEL\": \"claude-opus-4-7\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_HAIKU_MODEL\": \"claude-haiku-4-5\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Key Gotchas\n\n1. **`DISABLE_COMPACT=1` is mandatory** when using `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS` with non-Anthropic models. Without it, Claude Code ignores your custom context window and defaults to 200K.\n\n2. **Project-level `permissions` replace global permissions**, they don't merge. If you define a `permissions` block in `.claude/settings.json`, tools allowed globally will start prompting again unless re-listed.\n\n3. **Autocompact threshold is silently capped** at ~83% — you can only **lower** it from the default.\n\n4. **JSON comments (`//`) are not RFC 8259 compliant** — Claude Code may treat commented settings files as invalid. Remove them from production config.\n\n5. **Settings precedence**: Managed/Enterprise > Project-local (`settings.local.json`) > Project-shared (`.claude/settings.json`) > User (`~/.claude/settings.json`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Quick Reference: 200K Window with Early Compaction\n\n```json\n{\n  \"env\": {\n    \"CLAUDE_MAX_CONTEXT_WINDOW\": \"200000\",\n    \"CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT_OVERRIDE\": \"80\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis reduces the effective context per exchange from ~830K tokens (83% of 1M) down to ~160K tokens (80% of 200K) — roughly a **5× reduction** in per-exchange token volume, dramatically reducing cache misses and daily limit exhaustion.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"e7092a67-5bde-456e-b96f-d0699b31b7b2","timestamp":"2026-04-29T04:36:09.771Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Claude Code settings.json maxContextTokens context window override custom provider 2025 2026","results":[{"tool_use_id":"call_00_wCVLQW6SUrYpX3dUbcbBB2oQ","content":[{"title":"Add context window and autocompact configuration · Issue #213 · dcellison/kai","url":"https://github.com/dcellison/kai/issues/213"},{"title":"claude-code-best-practice/best-practice/claude-settings.md at main · shanraisshan/claude-code-best-practice","url":"https://github.com/shanraisshan/claude-code-best-practice/blob/main/best-practice/claude-settings.md"},{"title":"Claude Code详细配置指南：settings.json设置、多模型切换与可视化UI配置方法 - CSDN文库","url":"https://wenku.csdn.net/doc/azwsf5c5gb9z"},{"title":"GPT-5.5在claude code自定义上下文长度的方法","url":"https://www.locdd.com/t/topic/45015"},{"title":"Demo Environment and Configuration Management - KodeKloud","url":"https://notes.kodekloud.com/docs/Claude-Code-For-Beginners/Getting-Started-with-Claude-Code/Demo-Environment-and-Configuration-Management/page"},{"title":"配置参考","url":"https://claudecn.com/docs/claude-code/reference/settings/#%e4%b8%8b%e4%b8%80%e6%ad%a5"},{"title":"Model configuration - Claude Code Docs","url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/model-config"},{"title":"Configuration File Guide: Complete settings.json Reference","url":"https://lzw.me/docs/opencodedocs/affaan-m/everything-claude-code/appendix/config-reference/"},{"title":"Navigating Claude Code: The Bare Minimum Setup | HackerNoon","url":"https://hackernoon.com/navigating-claude-code-the-bare-minimum-setup"},{"title":"Claude Code CLAUDE.md vs settings.json: which one controls what (and why it matters)","url":"https://dev.to/subprime2010/claude-code-claudemd-vs-settingsjson-which-one-controls-what-and-why-it-matters-10i3#comments"}]},"# Claude Code Settings: Context Window & Custom Provider Configuration\n\nHere's a comprehensive synthesis of the search results covering `settings.json` configuration for context window overrides and custom provider setup, current through early 2026.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Context Window Control\n\n### Primary Environment Variables\n\nThese are set inside the `\"env\"` block of `settings.json` (or as OS env vars):\n\n| Variable | Purpose | Recommended |\n|---|---|---|\n| **`CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS`** | Hard-limit the context window in tokens (e.g., `\"400000\"` for 400K) | Overrides the default ~200K that Claude Code imposes on non-Anthropic models |\n| **`DISABLE_COMPACT`** | **Must be set to `\"1\"`** for `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS` to take effect. When disabled, automatic compaction and `autoCompactThreshold` are bypassed — you must manage compaction manually. | `\"1\"` |\n| **`CLAUDE_MAX_CONTEXT_WINDOW`** | Passed as `--max-context-window <N>` to the inner Claude process. Default 0 (uses Claude Code's default of 1M). | `\"200000\"` |\n| **`CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT`** | Percentage of context window at which autocompact fires. Default ~83%. Claude Code silently clamps values above ~83%. | `\"80\"` |\n| **`CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT_OVERRIDE`** | Upstream Claude Code env var name for the same autocompact threshold (used by some wrappers). | |\n| **`CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_1M_CONTEXT`** | Set to `\"1\"` to remove 1M context model variants from the model picker entirely. | `\"1\"` |\n\n### Example `settings.json` for a Non-Anthropic Model (e.g., GPT-5.5 with 400K context)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"env\": {\n    \"CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS\": \"400000\",\n    \"DISABLE_COMPACT\": \"1\",\n    \"DISABLE_AUTOUPDATER\": \"1\",\n    \"IS_SANDBOX\": \"1\"\n  },\n  \"enabledPlugins\": {\n    \"document-skills@anthropic-agent-skills\": true,\n    \"superpowers@claude-plugins-official\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\n> **Important:** When `DISABLE_COMPACT=1`, `autoCompactThreshold` is ignored. You must run `/compact` manually or risk exceeding the model's actual context limit.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Model & Provider Configuration\n\n### In `settings.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n  \"alwaysThinkingEnabled\": true\n}\n```\n\n- **`model`**: Accepts aliases (`sonnet`, `opus`, `haiku`), full model IDs, or the special `\"default\"` to clear overrides.\n- Extended context aliases: `sonnet[1m]`, `opus[1m]`.\n\n### Cloud Provider Env Vars (also set in `\"env\"` block)\n\n| Variable | Provider |\n|---|---|\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_BEDROCK` | AWS Bedrock |\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_VERTEX` | Google Vertex AI |\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_FOUNDRY` | Microsoft Foundry |\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_SKIP_BEDROCK_AUTH` | Skip Bedrock auth |\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_SKIP_VERTEX_AUTH` | Skip Vertex auth |\n\n### API Authentication (in `\"env\"`)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"env\": {\n    \"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\": \"sk-ant-api03-...\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"custom-auth-header\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_MODEL\": \"claude-opus-4-7\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_SONNET_MODEL\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_OPUS_MODEL\": \"claude-opus-4-7\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_HAIKU_MODEL\": \"claude-haiku-4-5\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Key Gotchas\n\n1. **`DISABLE_COMPACT=1` is mandatory** when using `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS` with non-Anthropic models. Without it, Claude Code ignores your custom context window and defaults to 200K.\n\n2. **Project-level `permissions` replace global permissions**, they don't merge. If you define a `permissions` block in `.claude/settings.json`, tools allowed globally will start prompting again unless re-listed.\n\n3. **Autocompact threshold is silently capped** at ~83% — you can only **lower** it from the default.\n\n4. **JSON comments (`//`) are not RFC 8259 compliant** — Claude Code may treat commented settings files as invalid. Remove them from production config.\n\n5. **Settings precedence**: Managed/Enterprise > Project-local (`settings.local.json`) > Project-shared (`.claude/settings.json`) > User (`~/.claude/settings.json`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Quick Reference: 200K Window with Early Compaction\n\n```json\n{\n  \"env\": {\n    \"CLAUDE_MAX_CONTEXT_WINDOW\": \"200000\",\n    \"CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT_OVERRIDE\": \"80\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis reduces the effective context per exchange from ~830K tokens (83% of 1M) down to ~160K tokens (80% of 200K) — roughly a **5× reduction** in per-exchange token volume, dramatically reducing cache misses and daily limit exhaustion."],"durationSeconds":52.34478610000003},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c6f692f1-19ca-4e41-a07b-016c1b3a783a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"d:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"07a593cf-bcb9-4bf9-a969-effe2aaab829","version":"2.1.123","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
