{"parentUuid":"78d28041-99b7-4273-a0e5-27d1b3c631d2","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"0fbcb71a-38d7-4ce0-ac73-b8a88abffffe","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The CLI produced no output. This might be a GUI-only application without a useful CLI interface.\n\nLet me try a fundamentally different approach. The core issue is that Claude Code, when connected to a non-Anthropic API through a proxy, defaults to 200K context. The `[1m]` suffix technique was supposed to work through cc-Switch, but it doesn't.\n\nLet me try these remaining approaches:\n\n1. Set `model` in settings.json to something with `[1m]` suffix\n2. Check if there are any other settings.json fields for context window\n3. Look at the actual Claude Code source/documentation for how context window is determined\n\nActually, wait - I just remembered something. Let me check if the user can set `ANTHROPIC_MODEL` in the env to include the `[1m]` suffix, and whether Claude Code reads this for context window determination. The earlier attempt added ANTHROPIC_MODEL but maybe it was overwritten by cc-Switch.\n\nAlso, I should look at Claude Code's actual source code behavior. Let me search more specifically.\n\nActually, let me think about this from a completely different angle. The `/context` command output shows `claude-sonnet-4-6` as the model. This is the model name Claude Code THINKS it's using. cc-Switch is proxying the API call to DeepSeek, but Claude Code still thinks it's talking to Claude Sonnet 4.6 with 200K context.\n\nThe question is: where does Claude Code get the `claude-sonnet-4-6` model name from? Either:\n1. From the API response (cc-Switch tells it this is the model)\n2. From settings.json env vars\n3. From internal defaults\n\nIf cc-Switch is reporting the model as `claude-sonnet-4-6` with 200K context, then that's what Claude Code will use regardless of `[1m]`.\n\nBut wait - if the model is `claude-sonnet-4-6`, why is the context 200K instead of 1M? Because Claude Code defaults to 200K for non-Anthropic providers, and it detects it's a non-Anthropic provider based on the base URL not being api.anthropic.com.\n\nHmm, but Claude Sonnet 4.6 actually supports 200K natively. The 1M variants are `claude-sonnet-4-6[1m]`.\n\nSo the real question is: can we trick Claude Code into thinking it's using a `[1m]` variant?\n\nLet me try setting `ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6[1m]` which would make Claude Code think it's the 1M variant, while cc-Switch ignores this model name and forwards the actual DeepSeek model.\n\nActually, we tried setting ANTHROPIC_MODEL earlier to `DeepSeek-v4-pro[1m]` and it didn't work. But what if we use the Claude model name with `[1m]` suffix?\n\nWait, the ANTHROPIC_MODEL env var is used by Claude Code to tell the API which model to use. But cc-Switch overrides this (the model parameter is controlled by cc-Switch). So setting ANTHROPIC_MODEL to a Claude model name won't help.\n\nActually, there's another possibility. Let me check the cc-Switch advanced config to see if it has a \"context window\" field per provider. The search results mentioned that cc-Switch v3.12.3 added a \"Codex 1M Context Window\" toggle, but maybe there's a similar setting for Claude Code.\n\nLet me try to access the cc-Switch GUI programmatically or check its database for available settings.\n\nActually, you know what, let me try a different approach entirely. What if we don't use cc-Switch and instead configure the DeepSeek API directly in settings.json? This would give us full control over the model and context window configuration.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"env\": {\n    \"ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL\": \"https://api.deepseek.com/anthropic\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"sk-deepseek-api-key\",\n    \"ANTHROPIC_MODEL\": \"deepseek-v4-pro\",\n    \"CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS\": \"1000000\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nBut the problem is we don't have the DeepSeek API key, and also we'd lose cc-Switch's model switching functionality.\n\nLet me go back to the drawing board and look at the Claude Code settings reference directly.\n\nActually, let me try one more thing: search for how Claude Code specifically determines context window size when using custom providers.","signature":"0fbcb71a-38d7-4ce0-ac73-b8a88abffffe"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":208,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":104448,"output_tokens":1208,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"type":"assistant","uuid":"3976f939-539b-49dd-a63f-f8f501b96178","timestamp":"2026-04-29T04:47:26.386Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"D:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"07a593cf-bcb9-4bf9-a969-effe2aaab829","version":"2.1.123","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
