{"parentUuid":"e0eb628d-9269-4389-98aa-45247cc8fa5f","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"198047df-da3c-4d55-bcc9-650157f4a69f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the search results show that `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS` is indeed a valid Claude Code env var, but it might need to be combined with `DISABLE_COMPACT=1` to actually take effect. Let me also try the `model` field in settings.json with `[1m]` suffix.\n\nBut wait - the user already tried with `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS=1000000` and it still showed 200K. The search also mentioned that `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS` is used to LIMIT (reduce) the context window, not to increase it beyond what Claude Code detects.\n\nThe fundamental issue is: Claude Code auto-detects the context window based on the model. When the base URL is not api.anthropic.com, it defaults to 200K. `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS` can lower this limit but apparently can't raise it.\n\nSo what actually SETS the context window in Claude Code? Let me think...\n\nLooking at the /context output: `claude-sonnet-4-6` is the model, and the context window is 200K. Normally `claude-sonnet-4-6` has 200K context (the 1M variant is `claude-sonnet-4-6[1m]`).\n\nSo the key insight: Claude Code sees the model as `claude-sonnet-4-6` (without `[1m]`), and therefore sets the context window to 200K. If we could make Claude Code see the model as `claude-sonnet-4-6[1m]`, it would be 1M.\n\nHow does Claude Code determine the model name? It comes from the API. cc-Switch must be telling Claude Code the model is `claude-sonnet-4-6`.\n\nSo the solution path is:\n1. Make cc-Switch report a `[1m]` model to Claude Code\n2. Or bypass cc-Switch's model reporting\n\nActually, looking at the cc-Switch logs earlier:\n```\n[Claude] >>> 请求 URL: https://api.deepseek.com/anthropic/v1/messages?beta=true (model=DeepSeek-v4-pro[1m])\n```\n\ncc-Switch is sending `DeepSeek-v4-pro[1m]` to the DeepSeek API, but it's reporting back to Claude Code as `claude-sonnet-4-6` (based on the /context output). So cc-Switch controls the model name that Claude Code sees.\n\nThis means the `[1m]` suffix needs to be on the Claude Code SIDE, not the DeepSeek API side. In cc-Switch, there might be a setting for the \"reported model\" or something similar.\n\nOK, let me try a completely different approach. Since `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS` seems to only reduce the context window (not increase it), let me try using the `model` field in settings.json.\n\nActually wait, I just had a key insight. Looking at the /context output more carefully:\n\n```\n⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛀ ⛁ ⛁   Sonnet 4.6\n⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛁ ⛀   claude-sonnet-4-6\n```\n\nThis means Claude Code thinks the model IS `claude-sonnet-4-6`. And `claude-sonnet-4-6` has 200K. The 1M variant is `claude-sonnet-4-6[1m]`. \n\nClaude Code 2.1.76+ (as mentioned in the cc-Switch docs) might have `ENABLE_TOOL_SEARCH` and other features. But the key thing is - cc-Switch is telling Claude Code \"this is claude-sonnet-4-6\" and Claude Code applies 200K.\n\nWhat if in cc-Switch's advanced config, we can specify the model name that's reported to Claude Code? Like `claude-sonnet-4-6[1m]`?\n\nBut actually, I wonder if this would break things because cc-Switch might use the model name to route requests.\n\nLet me think about ANOTHER approach. What if we don't use cc-Switch's proxy at all and instead use the DeepSeek API directly?\n\nThe user could:\n1. Add `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/anthropic` to settings.json\n2. Add `ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-xxx` \n3. Add `ANTHROPIC_MODEL=deepseek-v4-pro[1m]`\n\nBut the user may not want to lose cc-Switch functionality.\n\nActually, you know what, let me try one more thing. Let me check if the `model` field in settings.json can be set to a `[1m]` variant:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6[1m]\"\n}\n```\n\nThis might make Claude Code think it's using the 1M variant. cc-Switch would still route to DeepSeek based on its own configuration.\n\nActually this is the best bet. Let me try it.","signature":"198047df-da3c-4d55-bcc9-650157f4a69f"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1612,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":105856,"output_tokens":1305,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"type":"assistant","uuid":"c0f7e340-6ec0-45cd-8df9-db339a060360","timestamp":"2026-04-29T04:48:57.724Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"D:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"07a593cf-bcb9-4bf9-a969-effe2aaab829","version":"2.1.123","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
